         <notesStmt>
            <note>Folios 314-317 partly stained.</note>
            <note>Folios 1r-1v and 315v-317v: doodle pages. 
								Yitsḥaḳ Ḥazan of Furmicino and Shelomoh Yoshuʿa of Modena: inscribed in a contract of sale on folio 317v, with a date of  23 Tamuz 5355 (30 June 1595), at Ferrara. 
								Yeḥi᾿el Petaḥyah and Barukh ben Petaḥyah: inscribed several times on the flyleaves. 
								Luge Navaro, son of Eliezer Navaro de Ferrara: inscribed on folio 316v. 
								Luigi da Bologna, a converted Jew working for the Inquisition (active 1590-1609): inscribed with his name as censor, with a date of 1599, folio 315r, see 104. </note>
