                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 26 27;
                                                  written lines: 25 26; Uniform layout. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Visible complete ruling by hard-point, bifolium by bifolium (on hair side). Graphic fillers at the end of line, last written line within ruling. Truncated mem. The first word of each book is written in large ornamental letter, with addition of a pen and ink design in Kings.Omitted words are supplied and faulty readings are corrected in the margin.The beginning and the end of Haftarot are marked in the margin by a later hand.Fine Italian parchment, ruled on the hair-side with a hard point. No pricking is visible due to trimmed margins.Gilt edges.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Ashkenazi square script of  the 13th century (at variance with production area). Finished and punctuated by a different hand than the first books in the manuscript. Binyamin ben Yoʾav min ha-῾Anaṿim: inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 315r.</scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
